description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for a a senior Occupational Therapist to join our well established and highly motivated inpatient therapy teams at Arrowe Park Hospital and Clatterbridge Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have the opportunity to gain experience in working across our busy A&amp;E, assessment areas, medical inpatients, surgery and DME. There will be future opportunities to work across other inpatient areas; orthopaedics and neuro inpatients. This is a peripatetic role to respond to pressures across the inpatient service, however work is under way to develop Band 6 Rotations in the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and pro-active Occupational Therapist with post graduate experience in a range of core specialities including acute assessment, older persons assessment/frailty and medical inpatients. You should have excellent communication skills, be able to demonstrate a high level of clinical reasoning skills and be able to case manage patients with complex needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have professional support for your CPD from Band 7 Therapy team Leaders and support from Senior Occupational Therapists from other specialities as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post may also require working with the other inpatient therapy teams to provide senior therapy support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
